I loved BLOTTY but mostly for personal reasons.
BLOTTeh (pronounced BLO-tə) is the Yiddish word for mud or muck, and was the name for a family treat eaten on the eve of Passover. Take a beef broth mixed with mashed potatoes so that it is exactly midway between liquid and solid. If you're not sure whether to use a fork or a spoon, you're in the right spot. Add threads of the boiled beef and there you are - blotteh.

